@* EmployeeCard
   Why it exists: renders a reusable KPI card for summaries and dashboard stats.
   Component lifecycle: initial render shows placeholder values; parameters are supplied from the parent Dashboard after data loads.
   Data binding: the Title, Value, and Detail parameters are bound from parent component data.
   Event handling: this component is purely presentational and does not raise events.
   Dependency Injection: it has no injected services. It receives data from the parent by parameter binding.
   Routing: it does not participate in routing directly.
   API communication: it does not call the API itself; the parent dashboard loads data and passes summaries into the card.
*@
<div class="metric-card">
    <div class="metric-title">@Title</div>
    <div class="metric-value">@Value</div>
    <div class="metric-detail">@Detail</div>
</div>

@code {
    [Parameter]
    public string Title { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    [Parameter]
    public string Value { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    [Parameter]
    public string Detail { get; set; } = string.Empty;
}
